{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/nest-cli",
  "collection": "@nestjs/schematics",
  "sourceRoot": "src",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "deleteOutDir": true,
    "plugins": ["@nestjs/swagger"]
  }
}
```

---

🔁 How to Fix

1. Open apps/api/nest-cli.json
2. Replace its content with the JSON above.
3. (Optional) If you want to keep the file in the root of the monorepo instead of inside apps/api, adjust the paths accordingly. The standard NestJS setup expects nest-cli.json in the same directory as the API's package.json. For a monorepo, it's fine to have one per application.

---

❌ Problems with your current file

Issue Why it matters
"names": ["your-nest-app"] The correct collection is "@nestjs/schematics". This breaks nest generate commands.
No sourceRoot NestJS doesn't know where your source code is (defaults to src, but should be explicit).
No compilerOptions Without deleteOutDir, old compiled files may remain. Without Swagger plugin, DTO annotations won't generate proper docs automatically.

With the corrected file, you can now run:

```bash
nest generate resource users
nest generate service transactions
```

and the CLI will work as expected. 🚀
